latestIgtvVideos.title: Life at NERIM
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
“I've learned one thing, and that's to quit worrying about stupid things. You have four years to be irresponsible here, relax. Work is for people with jobs. You'll never remember class time, but you'll remember the time you wasted hanging out with your friends. So stay out late. Go out with your friends on a Tuesday when you have a paper due on Wednesday. Spend money you don't have. Drink 'til sunrise. The work never ends, but college does...”
― Tom Petty

latestPosts.caption:
The students of NERIM Group of Institutions participated in the Pool Campus Placement Drive by Bajaj Allianz General.

The drive was led by Mr. Sagar Saikia, Dr. Azizur Rahman ( Team from T&P Dept) and by Student Placement Coordinators- Mr Rupam Pathak and Mr. Mrinmoy Sarmah. It was wonderful to see the enthusiasm of our students where the recruiters appreciated the efforts and intense preparation of our students.

The drive culminated with seven final selections from NERIM.

NERIM Group of Institutions has bagged various awards from CSR, Times Now and NEWS18 Network in various categories such as:

1. Best Academic Leader for Excellence in Education- Prof ( Dr)Sangeeta Tripathi, Director , NERIM
2. Best Director- Prof ( Dr)Sangeeta Tripathi, Director , NERIM
3. Best Educational Institution in North -East India
4. Best Institution in Higher Education
and many more...

The awards received are a testament to the Institutions commitment in delivering quality education, with focus on skill based learning and upgradation. The Institution is also thankful to all its employees for standing together in all its phases. NERIM led by Prof.( Dr) Sangeeta Tripathi has achieved significant milestones during her tenure making it to be the best Institution across North East India.

The award ceremonies were attended by the Placement Team, Administrative Officers' and few of the faculty members.

latestPosts.caption:
Two of NERIM's employee: Mr. Sagar Saikia, Assistant Professor and Head- Training/ Placement and Dr. Azizur Rahman, Assistant Professor and TPO , participated as expert panel members at Education Conclave 3.0 hosted by the Times of India and Byatikram Group at Dimapur, Nagaland.

Both the faculty resources shared their view points on how to build a strong career path, identify significant milestones to reach to the ultimate goal, enlightened about the various ways of how to reasearch for various career avenues, highlighted Institutional responsibilities to help students identify their strengths and weaknesses, stressed to conduct impact study and skills identification tests to map relevant career endeavours, importance of academia- industry collaborations, significance of reskilling as per the need of market scenarios to many other important dimensions.

They shared their perspectives among various esteemed academicians, corporate leaders , bureaucrats, teachers and students. The points put forward by the faculty experts from NERIM was highly applauded by the participants and co-panel members for their thought provoking illustration of their content.

The two of panel members were also felicitated by the organizing committee for the strong and impactful deliberation.

The Education Conclave was graced by His Excellency, Shri La. Ganesan, Governor of Nagaland with many other high profile dignatries of East and North- East India.
